On 04/02/2011 04:16 PM, Djork-Arne Clevert wrote:
> Hi Martin,
>
> have many thanks for your help. I double-checked the DESCRIPTION file,
> but I
> couldn't find a mistake: both check and build went smooth and the
> version number
> should be ok, too.
> Please let me know what do I have to do, in order to fix this problem.

I think the Package: line ends with a new line only ('\n'; Linux) 
whereas your other lines end with carriage return and new line ('\r\n'; 
windows). This is throwing off an early stage in the build system, 
before R even sees the package. Remember that the build system only runs 
once a day so you will not know that you have been successful until the 
next build cycle.

Martin


